@Henry S please watch the part of video starting from 03:40:55. I have explained the equivalent circuit. This should explain why we have connected it to right side. 

We have used 10k resistance because we usually use high value resistance in such circuit. We can also use other value resistance. The purpose of this resistance is to prevent Arduino from reading float values.. float values means random values. 

0.5 mA came from ohms law. There is 5 V across 10k resistance. So the current flowing in it would be 0.5mA

